issues.message: Proposed changes do not address the failures described in the logs. The changes are in a test file, but the failures stem from assertions related to the actual implementation of the business logic in the server code.

risks: Changes could lead to misalignment between expected and actual outputs if the underlying implementation does not match the updated test expectations.
assumptions: It is assumed that the test failures are due to the implementation not returning the expected values, rather than an issue with the test itself.
